This paper is primarily focused on efficient model design for image classification and object detection on mobile devices, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques and optimization methods, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of NVIDIA TX2, which is a hardware platform for deep learning, and the optimization of the architecture for fast speed, which are relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
